  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for the Education in the Post-conflict Areas in Eastern Ukraine: in the way of Changes</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">During the project education quality improvement activities in three directions: students&#x2019; basic skills development, teachers&#x2019; competence development and reorganization of the educational process, improving methodical base of educational institutions, will be implemented in Luhansk and Donetsk regions. The Project Manager, together with authorities responsible for education in the region and other partners active in the field of education in Ukraine, will involve 60 children or young people from families affected from military actions and 50 teachers including educational administration also directly into the program. The school material and methodological base will also be increased by providing necessary for education equipment or access to the Internet.</narrative>
  </description>
